SMTP/HTTP Client Server Application

Features:

Utilizes c/c++ socket API to create a client and server using TCP. 

Built using the SMTP RFC, allowing a client to send commands to a server to create and process emails to other users within the server. 

Clients can download unread emails from server and have them stored locally using a HTTP GET request using the HTTP protocol and corresponding RFC.

Running the program:

running the makefile will create the files needed to run the program, the blank conf files should be set to a port before use
all files to run the program will be set within the app folder for better portability, allowing multiple instances over several containers.

to run the server, on a terminal, enter ./server server.conf to boot up the SMPT and HTTP servers.

Client side, in a different terminal/instance ./client client.conf will boot up the client



